                <head type="CCC">Raymond of Peńafort OP, Summa de casibus poenitentiae</head>
                <head type="James">Summa Raymundi</head>
                <p function="Codicology"><material>Vellum</material>, <measureGrp type="CCC">
                        <height unit="mm">145</height>
                        <width unit="mm">95</width>
                    </measureGrp>, <measureGrp type="James">5.7 x 4</measureGrp>, <extent>ff. 6 + 326 + 1</extent>,
                        <layout>double columns of 32 lines</layout>. Cent. <origDate>xiii-xiv early</origDate>,
                        <handNote>in fine hand</handNote>: <decoNote>admirable ornaments</decoNote>.</p>


                <p><label>Collation:</label>
                    <collation>a<num>6</num>, 1<num>16</num> 2<num>12</num> | 3<num>20</num>-13<num>20</num>
                            14<num>18</num> 15<num>20</num>-17<num>20</num> b (one)</collation>.</p>

                <p><label>2 fo.:</label>
                    <secFol>Clericus</secFol> or <secFol>de symonia</secFol>, or <secFol>a manu</secFol>.</p>


                <p function="Additions"><origDate>xvi</origDate>th and <origDate>xv</origDate>th cent. notes on f.
                        <locus>ir</locus> and f. <locus>iv</locus>. ff. <locus>iir</locus>-<locus>viv</locus> blank.</p>




                <p type="CCC">
                    <foliation>ff. a-b + i-vi + 1-326 + vii + c-d</foliation>.</p>


                <msContents>
                    <textLang mainLang="lat">Latin.</textLang>

                    <label>Contents</label>



                    <msItem n="1" locusStart="1r" locusEnd="326v">
                        <head type="CCC">
                            <name type="author">Raymond of Peńafort OP</name>, <title>Summa de casibus
                                poenitentiae</title>
                        </head>
                        <ab locus="1r">Table, Absolucio-Uxor, in single lines</ab>
                        <ab>
                            <handNote>Not in the hand of the text</handNote>
                        </ab>
                        <rubric locus="29r">Summa Raymundi</rubric>
                        <incipit locusNew="29r">Quoniam ut ait ieronimus secunda post naufragium tabula</incipit>
                        <ab locusNew="29r">
                            <decoNote>Initial. Tonsured man in blue with red hood kneels to hooded friar in brown over
                                white. Red ground, partial border. Exquisite work</decoNote>
                        </ab>
                        <ab>Text, liber I</ab>
                        <rubric locus="30r">De symonia</rubric>
                        <incipit locus="30r">Quoniam inter crimina</incipit>
                        <ab locusNew="30r">
                            <decoNote>Initial. Bishop stands on L. admonishing. Boy in C. tonsured holding bag of money.
                                He is pushed forward by a grey-bearded man on R. Church in C. in background. Blue
                                ground. Illustrates 'Simony'</decoNote>
                        </ab>
                        <ab locus="97v">Liber II</ab>
                        <rubric locusNew="97v">De homicidio</rubric>
                        <ab locusNew="97v">
                            <decoNote>Initial. Short-haired man in tunic with raised sword about to behead a kneeling
                                man on R. whose hair he clutches. Blue ground, patterned</decoNote>
                        </ab>
                        <ab locus="158v">Liber III</ab>
                        <rubric locusNew="159v">De qualitate ordinandorum</rubric>
                        <ab locusNew="159v">
                            <decoNote>Bishop in blue chasuble and mitre. Tonsured clerk in white kneels on R. The Bishop
                                holds his hand and speaks</decoNote>
                        </ab>
                        <ab>Ends</ab>
                        <explicit locus="287r">venite benedicti percipite regnum. Amen</explicit>
                        <rubric locusNew="287r">Explicit summa de penitentia</rubric>
                        <rubric locus="287r">Incipit prologus in librum quartum de matrimonio</rubric>
                        <incipit locusNew="287r">Quoniam frequenter in foro penitenciali</incipit>
                        <ab locusNew="287r">
                            <decoNote>Initial. <hi rend="italic">Noli me tangere</hi>. Magdalene kneels on L. Christ
                                with long cross-staff and raised hand. Blue ground</decoNote>
                        </ab>
                        <ab>Text</ab>
                        <rubric locus="288r">De sponsalibus</rubric>
                        <incipit locus="288r">Quoniam matrimonium</incipit>
                        <ab locusNew="288r">
                            <decoNote>Initial. Bishop in yellow chasuble joins the hands of a youth (L.) and maid (R.):
                                red ground</decoNote>
                        </ab>
                        <ab>Ends</ab>
                        <explicit locus="326v">corrigat et emendat</explicit>
                        <ab locusNew="viir">On the flyleaf at end are <origDate>xvth cent.</origDate> notes</ab>



                    </msItem>




